title: Moss Beach
name: Fitzgerald Marine Reserve
directions: park at the end of California Ave
hours: Park opens at 8AM, closing time varies by season
content: The Fitzgerald Marine Reserve is a unit of the San Mateo County Parks famous for its tide pools.  The best time to visit is during low tide when rocks are exposed and visitors can expect to find everything from starfish to the occasional octopus.  Seals are usually present on the beach as well.  Parking is limited and can be tough to find on weekends.  Docent tours are available.
